const e="vertical-spread-case-study",t="Vertical Spread Case Study",a="8 min",r=80,s="ðŸ“Š Spread Analyst",o=[{screen_type:"hook",visual:"nvda_chart_60days.png",headline:"Real trade. Real results. Real lessons.",text:"Let's dissect an actual bull call spread trade on NVIDIA from start to finish."},{screen_type:"definition",headline:"The setup: NVDA bull call spread",text:"Date: Oct 1. NVDA at $500. Thesis: AI momentum continues, target $550 by Dec. Trade: Buy Dec $500 call ($25), Sell Dec $550 call ($10). Net debit: $15 ($1,500). Max profit: $35 ($3,500). Max loss: $15 ($1,500). Breakeven: $515. Let's see what happened...",visual:"trade_ticket.png",highlight_words:["$500","$550","$15 debit","$35 max profit"]},{screen_type:"scenario",headline:"Days 1-14: Slow grind higher",question:"NVDA slowly climbs from $500 to $510. Your spread is now worth $18 (up from $15 entry). Profit: $3 per share ($300). That's 20% gain in 2 weeks. Some traders would close here. What would you do?",options:["Close and take the 20% profit","Hold - target is $550","Add to the position","Roll to higher strikes"],correct:1,xp_reward:10,explanation_correct:"In this case study, the trader held. Early profits are tempting, and taking 20% in 2 weeks is great. But if your thesis is intact, holding can pay off bigger.",explanation_wrong:"There's no 'wrong' answer here - taking 20% in 2 weeks is excellent. The trader held because the AI thesis remained intact. Let's see how it played out."},{screen_type:"scenario",headline:"Days 15-28: Market correction",question:"Broader market sells off. NVDA drops to $490 in 3 days. Your spread crashes to $10 (down from $18). You're now showing -$5 loss (-33%). What should you consider?",options:["Panic sell immediately","Review thesis - if intact, hold through volatility","Double down and add more","Switch to puts"],correct:1,xp_reward:10,explanation_correct:"Exactly! The trader reviewed: AI fundamentals unchanged, just market noise. Staying calm when your thesis is intact is crucial. This is where most traders panic-sell and miss the recovery.",explanation_wrong:"Volatility tests your conviction. If the thesis is intact and it's just market noise, staying calm is key. Panic selling locks in losses right before recovery."},{screen_type:"scenario",headline:"Days 29-42: Strong earnings + Recovery",question:"NVDA reports blow-out earnings. Stock gaps to $535, then grinds to $555 over the next week. Your spread is now worth $48 (max value is $50). Profit: $33 per share ($3,300). That's 220% gain. What now?",options:["Hold 17 more days for the last $2","Close for $48 - take 96% of max profit","Roll to January with higher strikes","Let it ride and hope for $50"],correct:1,xp_reward:10,explanation_correct:"Smart! You captured $33 profit (220% return). The last $2 isn't worth the risk of a reversal. Professional move: lock in 96% of max and move on.",explanation_wrong:"Greed is the enemy. You're up 220%. The last 4% of profit ($200) could vanish in one bad day. Take the win. This is why pros close at 50-75% - they know when to walk away."},{screen_type:"interactive_example",headline:"Alternative scenarios",description:"What if the trader made different decisions? Compare the outcomes.",inputs:[{label:"Original Trade",value:"Held from entry to 96% profit",locked:!0},{label:"Compare Scenario",type:"radio",options:["A) Closed at $18 (day 14)","B) Panicked at $10 (day 20)","C) Held to max $50 (day 60)"],value:"A"}],outputs:[{label:"Scenario A",value:"Profit: $300 (20%) | Time: 2 weeks | Annualized: ~520%"},{label:"Scenario B",value:"Loss: -$500 (-33%) | Time: 3 weeks | Lesson: Emotional decisions rarely work"},{label:"Scenario C",value:"Profit: $3,500 (233%) | Time: 8 weeks | Risk: Last 2 weeks were coin flip"},{label:"Analysis",value:"Scenario A is actually better risk-adjusted - taking 20% in 2 weeks beats 233% in 8 weeks"}],teaching_points:["Quick profits aren't bad - they free capital faster","Holding to max looks great in hindsight but is objectively risky","The actual trade (96% of max) was the professional choice"]},{screen_type:"summary_cards",headline:"Lessons from the case study",cards:[{front:"Entry lesson",back:"Had clear thesis (AI momentum), defined target ($550), calculated risk ($1,500). Never trade without this clarity."},{front:"Management lesson",back:"Stayed calm during 33% drawdown because thesis was intact. Avoided panic. This separates winners from losers."},{front:"Exit lesson",back:"Closed at 96% of max profit instead of gambling on last 4%. Professional traders always leave a little on the table."},{front:"Result",back:"220% return in 6 weeks. But more importantly: followed the plan, managed emotions, exited smart."}]},{screen_type:"celebration",xp_earned:80,total_xp:80,badge:"ðŸ“Š Spread Analyst",badge_description:"You can analyze trades like a professional",streak_bonus:!0,celebration_message:"You just learned more from one case study than most traders learn in months!",next_lesson_preview:{title:"Long Straddle",description:"Profit from big moves in ANY direction",unlock_status:"unlocked"}}],i={lesson_id:e,title:t,estimated_time:a,total_xp:80,badge:s,screens:o};export{s as badge,i as default,a as estimated_time,e as lesson_id,o as screens,t as title,r as total_xp};
